              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 73-year-old man from the Czech Republic who looks chronically unwell and tired, with a persistent cough that has been present for many months and episodes of shortness of breath after coughing fits [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:0]. He describes a heavy feeling in the chest and intermittent chest discomfort, symptoms that can occur with lung disease and are part of the current concern [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3, MEDDIALOG:C34.9:6]. Over the last two days, his family has also noticed new confusion, difficulty putting sentences together, and needing help with feeding, walking, and using the restroom [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7].\n\nHe is a retired industrial maintenance worker who spent decades around dusts and inhaled workplace agents, a plausible occupational exposure pattern relevant to lung cancer risk [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3]. He lives with his wife, and his adult daughter visits daily and has become increasingly involved because of the sudden change in his mental status [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7]. He used to enjoy gardening and short walks, but his stamina has dropped because of cough, fatigue, and breathlessness [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:0].\n\nAt home, {patientName} tries to stay independent, but his recent decline has made that difficult. The cough is often forceful and exhausting, and he brings up thick sputum at times [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:0]. His family is especially worried that the abrupt confusion could reflect spread of the cancer to the brain or a medication effect from strong pain patches started a few days ago [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7]."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:0e314529-3e59-4bd1-9b65-eed89e969f51",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has a history of chronic cough with periods of thick sputum production, fatigue, and breathlessness, symptoms that were concerning enough to warrant chest imaging in the diagnostic workup [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:0, MEDDIALOG:C34.9:5]. He recently started strong pain patches for cancer-related pain, and the family links the onset of confusion to the last few days after beginning this medication [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7].\n\nHis occupational background included years of exposure to inhaled industrial agents, a recognized risk factor for lung cancer [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3]. There is also a family history of lung cancer in his father [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7]. He has had declining exercise tolerance because of cough and shortness of breath [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:0]. No prior major procedures are essential to this presentation, and no additional comorbidities are specified by the evidence."
          }
        ]
      }
